Document: StreamPeerGZIP  
Path: godot/classes/class_streampeergzip.rst  
Summary: Class StreamPeerGZIP: A class for handling GZIP-compressed data streams.  

Inherits: StreamPeer < StreamPeerBase < Reference < Object  
Key Rule: StreamPeerGZIP is a specialized stream peer for decompressing and compressing data using the GZIP algorithm. It extends StreamPeerBase to provide GZIP-specific functionality for reading from and writing to compressed data streams.  

GDScript:  
```gdscript  
class_name StreamPeerGZIP extends StreamPeerBase  
```  

Key Rule: This class is used to interface with GZIP-compressed data, allowing for decompression of incoming data and compression of outgoing data. It is typically used in conjunction with other stream peers or network classes that handle raw byte streams.  

Key Rule: StreamPeerGZIP does not support direct file operations; it is designed for use with existing stream peers that provide the underlying byte data. Compression and decompression are handled internally by the class.  

Key Rule: When decompressing, data is read from the stream and automatically decompressed. When compressing, data written to the stream is automatically compressed using GZIP format.  

Key Rule: The class provides methods to check if the stream is compressed, to set compression level, and to handle errors specific to GZIP operations.
