Document: StreamPeerGZIP  
Path: godot/classes/class_streampeergzip.rst  
Summary: This class enables streaming compression and decompression of data using GZIP/deflate, ideal for network file transfers without full memory allocation.  

This class allows compressing or decompressing data using GZIP/deflate in a streaming fashion. It is particularly useful when handling files that need to be sent over a network without requiring full memory allocation. To use it, first start the stream via start_compression() (or start_decompression()). Once initiated, calling put_partial_data() on this stream will compress (or decompress) the data, writing it to the internal buffer. The method get_available_bytes() returns the number of pending bytes in the internal buffer, while get_partial_data() retrieves the compressed (or decompressed) bytes from it. When the stream concludes, finish() must be called to ensure the internal buffer is properly flushed. Before finalizing, check get_available_bytes() one last time to confirm if additional data remains to be read after flushing.
---CHUNK---
Document: StreamPeerGZIP  
Path: godot/classes/class_streampeergzip.rst  
Summary: Methods for managing GZIP compression and decompression streams, including initialization, finalization, and state management.  

- clear (void): No parameters.  
- finish (Error): No parameters.  
- start_compression (Error): use_deflate (bool, default false), buffer_size (int, default 65535).  
- start_decompression (Error): use_deflate (bool, default false), buffer_size (int, default 65535).  

clear: Clears this stream, resetting the internal state.  
finish: Finalizes the stream, compressing any buffered chunk left. You must call it only when you are compressing.  
start_compression: Start the stream in compression mode with the given buffer_size, if use_deflate is true uses deflate instead of GZIP.  
start_decompression: Start the stream in decompression mode with the given buffer_size, if use_deflate is true uses deflate instead of GZIP.